The Senior Special Assistant (to the President on Media and Publicity, Malam Garba Shehu, has expressed optimism that President Muhammadu Buhari will hand over to another government of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC). Nigeria records 26 Lassa fever deaths, 115 cases this year — NCDC Father impregnates teenage daughter in Bayelsa He spoke briefly on Wednesday during the post-Federal Executive Council (FEC) briefing while reacting to a question that suggested that the President had pushed the burden of fuel subsidy removal to the next administration with the plan to propose 18 months extension to the National Assembly for the implementation of the Petroleum Industry Act (PIA) originally scheduled to kick off this February. The presidential aide, who was told that the decision seemed as if the next administration had already been set up to fail, responded: “But she (The Minister of Finance, Budget and National Planning, Hajiya Zainab Ahmed) has answered you. Firstly, what this tells you is that the President is responsive and we are going to hand over to the next administration, APC, God willing.” The finance minister, who initially reacted to the question, said, “I know Mr President will be the President of Nigeria in December as well.”